  "prompt": "How do I use WhatsApp on a PC?",
  "response": "Using WhatsApp on your PC is convenient, especially when you want to type longer messages or access your chats while working on a computer. Here\u2019s how you can use WhatsApp on your PC:\n\n### **Method 1: WhatsApp Web**\n1. **Open WhatsApp Web**:\n   - Go to [web.whatsapp.com](https://web.whatsapp.com) on your computer\u2019s browser (Chrome, Firefox, Edge, Safari, etc.).\n\n2. **Open WhatsApp on Your Phone**:\n   - Open the WhatsApp app on your smartphone.\n\n3. **Link Your Phone to WhatsApp Web**:\n   - On **Android**: Tap the three-dot menu (\u22ee) > **Linked devices** > **Link a device**.  \n     On **iPhone**: Tap **Settings** > **Linked devices** > **Link a device**.\n   - Use your phone to scan the QR code displayed on your computer screen.\n\n4. **Start Using WhatsApp on Your PC**:\n   - Once the QR code is scanned, your WhatsApp chats will sync to your computer, and you can start messaging.\n\n---\n\n### **Method 2: WhatsApp Desktop App**\n1. **Download the App**:\n   - Download the WhatsApp Desktop app from [whatsapp.com/download](https://www.whatsapp.com/download).\n   - It\u2019s available for Windows and macOS.\n\n2. **Install and Open the App**:\n   - Install the app on your computer and open it.\n\n3. **Link Your Phone**:\n   - Open WhatsApp on your phone, go to **Linked devices**, and scan the QR code displayed in the desktop app.\n\n4. **Use WhatsApp on Your PC**:\n   - Your chats will sync, and you can start using WhatsApp on your computer.\n\n---\n\n### **Important Notes**:\n- Your phone needs to stay connected to the internet for WhatsApp Web or Desktop to work.\n- WhatsApp Web and Desktop are extensions of your phone app, so all messages are synced between devices.\n- You can use WhatsApp on up to four linked devices simultaneously.\n\nLet me know if you need further assistance! \ud83d\ude0a",
